### Brackets
* Understands HTML and CSS
* Plugins simplify your life


### Live Preview
* Click on the Lightening Bolt (upper right corner)


### Open Folder
* Use File menu, Open Folder
* Point to the top of your source code files
* Close Brackets and reopen to see your code
* Remove other Folders from list


### Beautify Plug-in
* Install in Brackets
* File menu, Extension Manager
* Beautify, Install
* In edit menu turn on "Beatify on Save"


### Emmet Plug-in
* Install in Brackets
* File menu, Extension Manager
* Search for Emmet
* [Emmet Website](https://emmet.io/)
* Download page, Select Brackets


### Use Emmet (html)
* Use CSS syntax to create HTML
* Tab is used to expand the HTML text

Type this then hit tab
```
html>head>title
```


### Use Emmet (html)
* Use CSS syntax to create HTML
* Tab is used to expand the HTML text

Expands to 
```
<html>
<head>
    <title></title>
</head>
</html>
```


### Use Emmet (header)
* Use CSS syntax to create HTML
* Tab is used to expand the HTML text

Type this then hit tab
```
body>header.banner>h1
```


### Use Emmet (header)
* Use CSS syntax to create HTML
* Tab is used to expand the HTML text

Expands to 
```
<body>
    <header class="banner">
        <h1></h1>
    </header>
</body>
```

### Use Emmet (card)
* Use CSS syntax to create HTML
* Tab is used to expand the HTML text

Type this then hit tab
```
.card>.card-header>.card-body>h1
```


### Use Emmet (card)
* Use CSS syntax to create HTML
* Tab is used to expand the HTML text

Expands to ...
```
<div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h1></h1>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
```


### Use Emmet (table)
* Use CSS syntax to create HTML
* Tab is used to expand the HTML text

Type this then hit tab
```
.summary>table.table.table-hover>tr>td
```


### Use Emmet (table)
* Use CSS syntax to create HTML
* Tab is used to expand the HTML text

Expands to 
```
<div class="summary">
    <table class="table table-hover">
        <tr>
            <td></td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</div>
```


